Description:
Ballistics of the 125mm Type-1 Tungsten APFSDS round for use on weapons of the D-81 family, including the ZPT-98-125. Designed in China and exported after 1992, did not enter widespread service with PLA. This entry represents charge design as manufactured and exported by the Pakistan State Arsenal.

Projectile: 125-1 7.37 kg
Charge: 9.35 kg Nitrocellulose (High Nitration, 1046.4 kJ/kg)
 - Main:        6.00 kg 16/19 Rosette
 - Incremental: 3.35 kg
  - 2.55 kg 16/19 Rosette
  - 0.8  kg 19/1-25
Combustible Cartridge: 1.12 kg (from D-81, 686.5 kJ/kg)
Specification:

 -   Pmcp: 475.6 MPa  549.17 MPa
Corrected: 530   MPa  615    MPa  (1.12x)
